The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

When the stars descended on the stage

The 67th Hero Honda BFJA Awards was more Tolly than 

Bolly. But there were far more grins than grumbles. Glimpses...

Prosenjt, who won the Best Actor award for Chokher Bali, 

did a special action number as a medley of his hit film songs played on the soundtrack

Rituparna Sengupta, Best Actress for Alo, in conversation 

with Lifetime Achievement winner Gulzar

Shaan was the singing star of the night as he rocked Salt 

Lake stadium with everything from Main aisa kyon hoon to It?s the time 

to disco to Koi kahe

Rajkumar Hirani and Vidhu Vinod Chopra won the top Bollywood 

awards for Munnabhai MBBS

Locket Chatterjee sizzled in her solo performance, part of 

the Charlie?s Angels act, co-starring June and Koneenica

Koel Mullick was the Most Promising Actress for her performance 

in Nater Guru. Seen here with family.

